= Annex: AZDZ-Club Member Agreement EN-US Translation

This agreement outlines the terms and conditions for individuals joining AZDZ-Club as members. By signing this document, the member agrees to abide by the following terms and conditions throughout their membership.

== 1. Membership Rights and Responsibilities

1.1. Members are entitled to participate in all club activities designated for members.  
1.2. Members may run for administrative roles after a minimum of three (3) months of active membership.  
1.3. Members must follow all instructions given by club coordinators or designated supervisors during activities.  
1.4. Membership is valid only while the individual remains a full-time student at *Technische Hochschule Deggendorf (THD)*.  
1.5. Members are obliged to inform the club coordinator/secretary within six (6) months if their study program at THD has ended.

== 2. Media and Publicity Consent

2.1. Members consent that photos taken during club activities may be used for the club’s social media, repositories, and promotional materials.  
2.2. Such photos will be used and issued under the Creative Commons Attribution-NoDerivatives 4.0 (CC-BY-ND 4.0) licence.  
2.3. Members may use photos and materials from club activities for personal blogs or professional profiles (e.g., LinkedIn) under applicable licenses. They must indicate that the activity was conducted by AZDZ-Club and credit the organizer appropriately.  
2.4. The activity should not be misrepresented or misused in any manner.

== 3. GitHub Organization and Code Licensing

3.1. Members consent to being added to the club’s GitHub organization.  
3.2. Any code, documentation, or materials developed within the club are issued under the license indicated in the respective repository.  
3.3. Members agree to abide by the repository’s licensing terms when using or contributing to club projects.

== 4. Equipment Usage and Responsibility

4.1. Members may borrow club equipment only if an authorized personnel has been notified and the lending period is recorded in writing.  
4.2. The borrowing period is valid until the next earliest club activity, where the equipment must be returned.  
4.3. Extension of the borrowing period is permitted only with authorization from club personnel.  
4.4. Members are responsible for any damages or defects found upon return of the equipment.  
4.5. Members must not pass equipment to another person or club member.  
4.6. Any damage occurring during the rental period must be reported immediately. Members may be financially liable for damages if deemed necessary.  
4.7. Violating the equipment lending rules twice will result in the member losing their borrowing privileges.

== 5. Electronics and Lab Safety Compliance

5.1. Members confirm they have completed the Lab Safety Instructions Course and are authorized to work in the lab.  
5.2. Members agree to follow all safety procedures when handling electronic components, circuits, and tools.  
5.3. Any unauthorized tampering with lab equipment, power sources, or sensitive components is strictly prohibited.  
5.4. Members must return all borrowed tools and components to their original place after use.  
5.5. Any modifications or custom-built circuits must be approved by a club supervisor before connection to power sources.  
5.6. Members are prohibited from entering restricted lab areas or handling hazardous materials without prior authorization.  
5.7. Any use of chemicals, soldering irons, or high-voltage systems must be under supervision.  
5.8. Any violation of safety procedures may result in suspension or termination of membership.

== 6. Use of Personal Information

6.1. Members’ email addresses, GitHub accounts, names, and other shared details will be used strictly for core club activities, including notifications for club events and other non-promotional purposes.  
6.2. Personal details will not be shared with third parties, except for Faculty EMT of THD for administrative purposes.

== 7. Respect for Club and University Property

7.1. Any damage to club or university property due to negligence may result in financial liability.  
7.2. Equipment should not be disassembled or modified without approval.

== 8. General Conduct and Compliance

8.1. Members must conduct themselves respectfully and professionally during all club activities.  
8.2. Violations of the club’s guidelines may result in disciplinary actions, including suspension or removal from the club.  
8.3. The club reserves the right to modify activity rules and membership requirements as necessary.

